My hospice dog turned 16, PJ turned 2, and it was MrsPuckett's adoption anniversary all in the same week</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/o0dsf03.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I still get pretty nervous posting here sometimes, so I wanted to thank everyone for helping out with Puckett Week and all the nice comments and messages the last 7 days</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hW6s7aE.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>As most of you know, I love showing off pictures of my little dogs running all over Nashville</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/AigW4nV.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>And showing off all the progress my hospice dog is making since we adopted her in July</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bxGBx57.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>All this week we've been sending goods and raising funds for domestic violence survivors facing homelessness.

In mainly $16 donations, we've raised over $12,000 in only 6 days!!!!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SAiwT2k.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Domestic violence is the leading cause of homelessness for women and children in America. 

I was super happy to find The Mary Parrish Center who offers free housing and support to survivors, everything they might need to start their life fresh and stay off the street.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9VdsC1F.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It's like this oasis of incredibly nice apartment homes that survivors can stay in for up to a year to get their life back together with their children and dogs.

When they feel safe enough to move out on their own, they even get to take all of the furniture and everything inside their apartment at Mary Parrish.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/OZtCjTq.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Today is the final day of Puckett Week. It's been an incredible week of support from everyone seeing these posts

Not only the donations and sending items to survivors off the Wishlist, but everyone being so supportive of me and everyone else in the comments.

If it makes me feel this good, imagine how it'll make survivors feel when they get out of an abusive relationship, out of a shelter and into their new safe apartment.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7DWKt1y.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>So while this is probably my last post for a while, I can't thank everyone enough for making all of this possible. For one final time in Puckett Week 2022 -

If you would like to donate $16 in honor of Nanna's 16th birthday -

https://www.maryparrish.org/donate

You can also send items directly to residents at Mary Parrish on their Wishlist here -

https://www.amazon.com/hz/wishlist/ls/3USHUHIVSINQE?ref_=wl_share

...

I love you, thank you all so much for being there for me and being there for survivors.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Mlat7Ew</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MrPuckett]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Awesome comeback!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Jr0FKXM</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/LeQKzaG.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Jr0FKXM</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[0lm3ca]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Took his shot</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/mUBCAx4</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/S9XPuiP.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/mUBCAx4</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[yougotjamed]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I have to agree that most people do not realize the strength it takes.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/SvIJJyY</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MsHEPAM.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/SvIJJyY</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ice2Ice2]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>American Health 'Care' System</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/9AKk9pR</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JqCrnlu.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://twitter.com/jackiembouvier/status/1495546570548432901</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/9AKk9pR</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[GlobalImageServiceCat]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Good mom :)</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/sm8KDjL</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/EybyLKg.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Source : https://instagram.com/canecorso