dth: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/nM0jYfK</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[yougotjamed]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>My art is heading to a museum!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/gUp7qK1</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pbrW4OP.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Okay friends, I'm pretty excited about this. I build 1/25 scale dioramas, all involving the history of illegal alcohol and Prohibition. My family went back a generation making it in Pulaski County, Virginia. 

So, they got noticed on social media. Now, 'Moonshine Number One' and 'Moonshine Number Two' will go on display in North Carolina at the Wilkes Heritage Museum in their Moonshine History exhibit. Kinda excited about this one! It's like watching your kids succeed! I dunno. ?

#FifteenMinutesOfFame

https://www.blueridgeheritage.com/.../wilkes-heritage.../</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TiIp5qi.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/yA7aptw.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/QnshpTz.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/AmRft2q.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/gUp7qK1</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[JowesCrow]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Repost</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/EEQ3jkp</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/n3Sn5FH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/EEQ3jkp</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Lady007hash111]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>What a ride.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/h6YgDIc</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RWyEoA1.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>In December my manager took an extended bereavement after his eldest son committed suicide. I took over his position w/ pay bump while he was gone. While he was out I made sure to get things taken care of such as getting tools that we were in desperate need of replacing, and getting proper maintenance done to equipment ect. I fired one guy who was highly toxic, and a legal liability in our shop who the manager refused to fire because he had been in the shop for over 10 years. (Do not care 10 years or 50 years) he was extremely bad. Sexist, racist, and was a danger to himself and others because of his behavior. Hired an amazing replacement for him, and put in many long hours making sure all went well. My manager returned last Monday, and I went back to my hourly supervisor position. The bad news is today is my last day in my shop. The regional manager took note of my work and I was offered a permanent salaried position in a new shop which opens Thursday. I live 5 minutes from my current shop, but the new shop is only a 15 minute drive from my place currently. So I do not have to move. I am excited to start my new position there.  EDIT:
Sorry I think I messed up on the penguin. And my manager for another 2 hours is a good one. Unfortunately corporate has a convoluted system of getting tools, and equipment repaired, but I figured out the ins and outs took advantage of it and got the shop fixxed up better. He also is currently seeing a therapist about the whole ordeal and told me several times he was glad I accepted the step up he did teach me what he knew and I showed him how to work the system to get things fixxed. He is happy for me and they the guys in the shop threw me a going away party during lunch. Unbeknownst to one he is going to get a chance to be the paid supervisor in my new shop. When I say new I mean they finished construction two weeks ago and grand opening is Thursday. Tommorrow I have to go in on my day off to offer the position to him.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/h6YgDIc</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[retailmemedrone]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Geometry</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/EH559m4</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/gw9rrs0.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/t3luKO3.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/BUfim08.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/o1t7ST8.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/EH559m4</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[vidadobl6]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>woodworking trick</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/9ujiRGf</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/H1IJ26i.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/9ujiRGf</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[woodworking720]]></dc:c